A Polokwane
businessman was shot dead at Mahlatse Fast Food on Church Street, on Wednesday
night. It’s
alleged that the man walked into the shop without saying anything, he then
pulled out a gun and shot the 57-year-old businessman. He
reportedly ran into a Ford Ranger, and he sped off from the scene. Police
spokesperson Captain Mamphaswa Seabi said they were called to the scene
and manhunt operation ensued.  “The
motive behind this incident is unknown,” Seabi said. Seabi urged anyone with more information about the incident, to contact Captain
Otto at 0825758073 or 0860010111.    